There is a max payload size for sending binary data in tomcat, i.e. `org.apache.tomcat.websocket.binaryBufferSize` referred from [tomcat doc][1]. The default value of it is `8192`. So the `capacity` must be less than or equal to this value.

So your code must be modified to something like this

`int capacity = session.getMaxBinaryMessageBufferSize();`

Now, increase the size of `org.apache.tomcat.websocket.binaryBufferSize` to some reasonably higher value, this may increase data transfer speed and thus the download speed.

You can change this value using context initialization parameter in `web.xml`.

Eg:

    &lt;context-param&gt;
        &lt;param-name&gt;org.apache.tomcat.websocket.binaryBufferSize&lt;/param-name&gt;
        &lt;param-value&gt;16384&lt;/param-value&gt;
    &lt;/context-param&gt; 


  [1]: https://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-9.0-doc/web-socket-howto.html

